# Resume Command: `/codedpixels resume`

When the user message is **`/codedpixels resume`** or **`CODEDPIXELS RESUME`** (case-insensitive):

## 1. Become Nathan

State: **"Operating as Dr. Nathan Cole — resume protocol."**

## 2. Load checkpoint (mandatory reads)

- `docs/planning/project-status.md`
- `docs/planning/ticket-deliverables.md`
- `docs/planning/implementation-tickets.md` (current + next wave sections)

## 3. Verify completed work (do not trust status file alone)

Run in shell:

```bash
git log -5 --oneline
git status
git rev-parse HEAD
```

For **each ticket** listed as completed in `project-status.md`:

- Confirm deliverable paths from `ticket-deliverables.md` exist (`test -f` or glob)
- Confirm commit SHA matches or is ancestor of current HEAD
- If **missing** → mark ticket **NOT verified**, remove from trusted complete set, report gap

If `package.json` exists:

```bash
npm test
```

**All tests must pass** before continuing past verified waves. Fail → stop, report, assign fix.

## 4. Decide next work

| Situation | Action |
|-----------|--------|
| Completed tickets fail verification | Reopen failing ticket; do **not** spool next wave |
| In-progress handoffs in status file | Collect/verify handoffs; run wave close if all ready |
| Current wave incomplete | **Spool parallel agents** for unblocked tickets in `Next parallel spool` table |
| Current wave all verified, not committed | Nathan runs wave close: full test + build → commit + push → update `project-status.md` → **auto-spool next wave** |
| Wave committed + pushed, status stale | Update `project-status.md` then **auto-spool next wave** (no user prompt) |
| Wave committed + pushed, status current | **Auto-spool** unblocked tickets for **Current wave** |

## 5. Output format (required)

```markdown
## Resume summary
- Wave: N | Last SHA: abc123 | Tests: pass/fail/n/a

## Verified complete
- ENG-XXX: OK (files listed) / FAILED (what's missing)

## Next parallel spool
- [ticket list with lanes]

## Action now
[what Nathan does next — wave close + push + auto-spool / fix ticket X — never "ask to spool next wave"]
```

## 6. Never on resume

- Skip verification because status file says done
- Start a ticket blocked by gates (ENG-006 before Wave 3 UI, etc.)
- Commit/push without full test suite green (Nathan only)

Append one line to **Resume verification log** in `project-status.md` when done.
